# Monorepo single env file (repo root). Copy to `.env` and edit; never commit `.env`.
# Docker Compose and `scripts/docker-*.sh` read this path. Next + sync-api load it in dev (see below).
#
# =============================================================================
# Local development — web + Electron (what to have in mind)
# =============================================================================
#
# 1) MongoDB — sync-api needs a reachable URI (default in code: mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017).
#    Typical: `docker compose --profile local-mongo up -d mongo-sync` then set MONGODB_URI below
#    to match (compose service hostname is `mongo-sync` only inside Docker; on the host use
#    127.0.0.1:27017).
#
# 2) sync-api — `npm run sync-api` from repo root loads THIS file via apps/nodex-sync-api.
#    Set JWT_SECRET (≥32 chars in production; dev can use the commented example).
#    PORT/HOST default to 4010 / 0.0.0.0. CORS defaults to permissive in dev so Next on :3000
#    can call sync-api on :4010.
#
# 3) Next web — `npm run dev:web` already sets NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_WPN_USE_SYNC_API=1 and
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_WEB_BACKEND=sync-only. The client resolves the sync base to
#    http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1 in development when NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL is unset
#    (see packages/nodex-platform resolve-sync-base). If you use the Docker gateway on :8080,
#    set NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1 (must include /api/v1).
#    For same-origin through nginx only: NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1.
#
# 4) Electron — dev shell loads the Next app from NODEX_WEB_DEV_URL (default http://127.0.0.1:3000),
#    so run `npm run dev:web` before or with `npm start` / `npm run electron`. File vault + IPC
#    do not need sync-api unless you use Cloud/sync features; optional vars below (RxDB mirror,
#    WPN-only file vault) apply to desktop only.
#
# =============================================================================
#
# --- Local npm (web + sync-api only; skips slow electron-rebuild on `npm install`) ---
# NODEX_SKIP_ELECTRON_REBUILD=1
# Or once: `npm run install:web` / `npm run ci:web`. Electron: `npm run rebuild:electron`
#
# --- Electron ADR-016 (local RxDB mirror + optional renderer authority) ---
# Mirror: after each main `nodex-workspace.json` persist, main pushes a debounced payload to the renderer;
# renderer hydrates RxDB snapshot + normalized WPN collections and can serve WPN reads via `getNodex()` overlay.
# NODEX_LOCAL_RXDB_WPN=1
# Authority: main `WorkspaceStore.persist()` no-ops; renderer must call `Nodex.flushWorkspaceRxdbMirrorToDisk(payload)`
# with the same v1 mirror shape (set in main process env when launching Electron).
# NODEX_WORKSPACE_RXDB_AUTHORITY=1
#
# --- Docker / deploy (Compose interpolates ${VAR} from this file) ---
# Local mongo container: omit when MONGODB_URI points at remote DB (not *mongo-sync*); deploy defaults NODEX_LOCAL_MONGO=0 then.
# Force compose Mongo anyway: NODEX_LOCAL_MONGO=1
# NODEX_LOCAL_MONGO=0
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USER:PASS@CLUSTER.example.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
# MONGODB_DB=nodex_sync
# JWT_SECRET=minimum-32-characters-for-production-signing-key
# NODEX_GATEWAY_PORT=8080
# COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=nodex
#
# --- sync-api (local `npm run sync-api` and defaults when not overridden by Compose) ---
# PORT=4010
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017
# MONGODB_DB=nodex_sync
# JWT_SECRET=change-me-minimum-32-characters-long
# CORS_ORIGIN=true
# Optional: smaller Mongo pool for serverless (also set automatically when VERCEL=1 on Next `/api/v1`).
# NODEX_SYNC_API_SERVERLESS=1
# Optional: enable Fastify request logging when Next serves colocated `/api/v1` (off by default on Vercel).
# NODEX_SYNC_API_VERBOSE=1
#
# --- Next web (`npm run dev:web` / Dockerfile.web build args; use NEXT_PUBLIC_* only) ---
# Sync client calls paths like `/auth/register` relative to this base — it must end with `/api/v1`
# (e.g. `http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1`). A bare `http://127.0.0.1:4010` yields 404 on `/auth/register`.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_WPN_USE_SYNC_API=1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_WEB_BACKEND=sync-only
# Force sync client to use the browser tab origin + /api/v1 (nginx gateway on same host).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1
# If unset: opening a non-loopback host (e.g. nodex.studio) while NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL
# still points at 127.0.0.1/localhost is auto-corrected to same-origin /api/v1 in the client.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_API_SAME_ORIGIN=0
#
# Next production metadata (canonical URL for OG / absolute links). Use your real public origin (no path).
# On Vercel, `VERCEL_URL` is a fallback at build time if unset (preview URLs); set SITE_URL for a stable canonical domain.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SITE_URL=https://your-app.example.com
#
# When web and sync-api share the same public host (one full-stack deploy, API under `/api/v1`):
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SITE_URL=https://your-app.example.com
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_SYNC_API_URL=https://your-app.example.com/api/v1
# (`SITE_URL` = origin only; `SYNC_API_URL` = same host + `/api/v1` — required shape for the client.)
# CSP `connect-src` already includes `'self'`, so same-origin fetch works even if you omit SYNC and use
# NEXT_PUBLIC_NODEX_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1 instead; setting both explicit URLs is still fine and documents intent.
#
# Optional: `1` serves `robots.txt` with disallow all (private / staging deployments — same env file can use same URLs above plus this).
# NODEX_ROBOTS_NOINDEX=1
#
# --- Electron file vault (Track A legacy removal) ---
# When 1, `WorkspaceStore.persist` writes empty `legacy` and note IPC skips flat-store fallbacks (WPN-only on disk).
# NODEX_WPN_ONLY_FILE_VAULT=1
# Set to 0 to skip automatic legacy flat tree → WPN migration on eligible project open (default: migrate when eligible).
# NODEX_MIGRATE_LEGACY_FLAT_TO_WPN=0
#
# --- MCP: local loopback WPN bridge (Electron main; used by `packages/nodex-mcp` with NODEX_LOCAL_WPN_*) ---
# After opening a folder vault, main listens on 127.0.0.1 only. Token file: userData/nodex-local-wpn-mcp.json
# NODEX_WPN_LOCAL_HTTP=1
# Optional fixed port (default: ephemeral port chosen by OS).
# NODEX_WPN_LOCAL_HTTP_PORT=41234
# Optional shared secret; if unset, a token is generated and stored next to the JSON file above.
# NODEX_LOCAL_WPN_TOKEN=
#
# --- MCP: cloud session + browser device login (sync-api + `packages/nodex-mcp`) ---
# Interactive cloud MCP: allow startup without NODEX_ACCESS_TOKEN; use nodex_login / nodex_login_browser_* tools.
# NODEX_MCP_CLOUD_SESSION=1
# Persist access+refresh under XDG_CONFIG_HOME or ~/.config/nodex/mcp-cloud-auth.json (0600). Override path:
# NODEX_MCP_AUTH_FILE=
# Optional AES-256-GCM wrapping (set a long random secret); file on disk is not plaintext when set.
# NODEX_MCP_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
# Public origin for /mcp-auth links returned by POST /auth/mcp/device/start (production: your Next site URL).
# NODEX_MCP_WEB_VERIFY_BASE=https://your-app.example.com
#
# --- Next: legacy /api/v1 proxy (local only in practice) ---
# Rare: rewrite /api/v1 to another origin (see apps/nodex-web/next.config.mjs). Leave unset for Option B.
# NODEX_HEADLESS_API_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:9999
# On Vercel, HEADLESS is ignored unless you explicitly opt in (avoids 404 on new colocated routes):
# NODEX_ALLOW_HEADLESS_REWRITE_ON_VERCEL=1
